Ask HN: Why aren't SQL queries compiled?
text: If the database knew what queries were running ahead of time and have them compiled you could easily defend against SQL injection because the SQL isn't being interpreted as it's run, and  it would be possible to run analysis over the query to see if there are any indexes or implementations missing that could speed it up. Something like a stored procedure's variable substitution but not interpreted when called.

Ask HN: What comment-system do you recommend for a static blog?
text:
Currently I'm using Disqus, but it's now adding 10 huge clickbait thumbnails on every page. And $11/month doesn't seem worth the cost to remove them...

I'm interested in other alternatives, hopefully easy to integrate like Disqus was. Also interested if comments can be migrated too.
